1. Program Execution : 

(i) Run the command "make". It will create the required Class Files.
(ii) Execute : java Solution  -df $disount-factor -tol $tolerance-value -itr $maximum-number-of-iterations [-min] $file-name

Example : java Solution -df .9 -tol 0.0001 test1.txt
Note : In the abopve command the test1.txt file is in the same folder as Solution.java

2. Input Specifications : 
-df : Discount Factor must be in the range [0,1]
-tol : Allowed Tolerance
-iter : Maximum Allowed Iterations
-min : Set to true to minimize the costs.
